Moody's Investors Service Inc said itdowngraded to Ba-2 from Baa-3 Southdown Inc's 140 mln dlrs ofsenior debt.    The agency also assigned an initial rating of B-1 to thecompany's 90 mln dlrs of senior subordinated notes due 1997.    Moody's said the action reflected increased leverage andreduced interest resulting from lower earnings. It also citedSouthdown's repurchase of 28 pct of its common stock and thefinancing of that transaction by debt.    Moody's said the lower ratings anticipate certain debtreduction in the coming year from the sale of assets. Reuter&#3;